{% endif %}

## Rules

{% if profile.api.api_style == 'rest' %}
1. Follow RESTful resource naming conventions (plural nouns, e.g. `/users`, `/orders`)
2. Use appropriate HTTP methods: GET (read), POST (create), PUT/PATCH (update), DELETE (remove)
3. Return appropriate HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 401, 403, 404, 500)
4. Include pagination for list endpoints
{% elif profile.api.api_style == 'graphql' %}
1. Follow existing GraphQL schema conventions
2. Use query batching and fragments to minimize requests
3. Implement proper error handling in resolvers
4. Add authorization at the resolver level, not the schema level
{% else %}
1. Follow existing API conventions
2. Use consistent request/response formats
3. Include proper error handling
{% endif %}

